CTC TECHNOLOGY (CTCT) - A leading maintenance and operational service provider



 





Contact














Supporting Japan's social infrastructure as a core company of the CTC Group which has a customer base of approximately 8,000 firms, including the leading companies in all industries.
Whether it is constantly evolving mobile phones with new functions and advanced technologies, enormous portal sites with innumerable accesses every day, or online brokerages requiring utmost security, CTC TECHNOLOGY supports the large-scale systems on which these businesses are based. 


Service&Solutions
Based on our solid track record and wealth of expertise, we respond to our customers' needs and objectives with one-stop services.




Maintenance Service
Providing prompt services with a full 24/7 support system and almost 100 service locations nationwide.


Management Service
A team of engineers skilled in customer systems provides system operation and failure support, with top priority on business continuity.


IT Facility Service
Planning ahead for businesses, we build the optimal infrastructure for offices and data centers.

Technical Education Service
We regularly run more than 500 public courses including Vendor Certification Courses, CTC TECHNOLOGY Original Courses, etc.








Strengths of CTCT
Supporting mission-critical large-scale systems with outstanding technical expertise. 



As a core company of the CTC Group, we provide seamless services in four areas including maintenance, management, IT facility works, education and training, offering a broad range of one-stop services in maintenance and operations throughout the IT life cycle of our customers' systems.


We provide strong support for our customers' systems by forging solid partnerships with leading IT companies around the world as a member of the CTC Group and by maintaining leading technical expertise in Japan through a wide range of internal training systems.


We have centralized our point of contact for customers. We centrally manage our customers' entire services by sharing information smoothly with a nationwide call management system, continuing to provide one-stop services in a standardized format across the nation.





